    "visualization_explanation": "This 4x4 matrix heatmap uses categorical axes for color inputs (x) and vision types (y). The synthetic color mappings follow color deficiency simulation algorithms, maintaining hue relationships while introducing characteristic confusion patterns. Normal vision colors use primary hex codes, while modified colors reflect established color blindness profiles: Deuteranomaly (green-weak) shows red-brown shifts, Protanopia (red-blind) demonstrates blue-yellow dominance, and Tritanopia (blue-blind) exhibits green-pink inversion. The design maximizes data-ink ratio by eliminating legend and gradients, directly encoding perceptions through cell coloring. Perceptual effectiveness is achieved through Cairo's principle of discriminable colors, using WCAG-compliant contrast ratios between adjacent cells. The tooltip enhances precision with both color swatches and hex codes, supporting accurate interpretation across vision types."
